    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline>Feb.1.1779</dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>The best way will be to advertise twice in two different papers the <rs ref="ar0008">Print</rs> &amp; <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">the
                            Welsh Tour</title></bibl> &amp; <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora Scotica</title></bibl>. which will shew that
                        <persName ref="pe0192">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Elliot</persName> now
                    is authorised to act for me. He must acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> to me at
                    Christmas for the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">Tour</title></bibl>
                    at 16<hi rend="superscript">S</hi> per copy. the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora</title></bibl> at 12.<hi rend="superscript">S</hi>
                    the <rs ref="ar0008">Prints</rs> at 3<hi rend="superscript">S</hi>â€”<hi rend="superscript">D</hi>6. for I desire but one reckoning annually. I have
                    ordered 25 <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">Tours</title></bibl> to be
                    sent to him by waggon let him procure the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora</title></bibl> by virtue of the inclosed.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am in much haste <lb/>truely y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed></closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>I continue with <persName ref="pe0026">White</persName> no longer than I can
                        help.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House.</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
        </body>
